### Form Building 

## Which of these fields are required to be marked as Sensitive Data? 

 Bank Account Fields

 Social Security Numbers

 Password Fields

 **Credit Card Fields**

## Which of these statements about menu dependent fields and conditional fields are correct?

 Menu dependent fields do not change depending on the selection in a previous field, while Conditional fields do.

 Conditional fields are always required.

 **Menu dependent fields consist of a parent field and a child field.**

 **Conditional fields are hidden or visible based on set rules.**

 Menu dependent fields consist of a trigger and a field that is visible or hidden depending on the settings.

## Which of these field types allows the respondent to select multiple options in one field? 

 **Checkbox**

 Conditional Field

 Dropdown Menu

 Radio Button

## Which of these do you use to set up custom validation?

 HTML

 **Regex**

 CSS

 JavaScript

## Which of these is not a method that you can use to organize your form fields? 

 Drag and drop fields in the Form Builder canvas.

 Drag and drop fields in the Outline.

 Drag and drop fields from the Add Content menu.

 **Drag and drop fields in the form's Preview.**







## Does our Support Team assist with writing and editing custom code?

 **No**

 Yes



## Which one of these variables is invalid?

 variableOne

 Xnqdidbcjef

 varIABLE

 **Variable1**



## Which of these can NOT be made repeatable?

 **Text and Headings**

 Fieldset

 Dropdown Menu

 **Page**



## How can you make an image in your form conditional?

 **Add the image to a section and then make the section conditional.**

 It is not possible to use conditional images in your form.

 Set the Conditional Rules in the editing sidebar.

 Click on the image to add the Conditional Rules directly.

## Is it possible for a respondent to edit a calculated field?

 Yes

 **No**



## Is it possible to directly edit the code of the theme?

 Yes, you can use custom CSS to add customization.

 **Yes, if you are an Enterprise or Compliance Cloud admin.**

 No, it is not possible.



## Which of the following are available Public themes? 

 **All of these**

 Polar

 Cloud

 Stormy Sea

 Arctic Air

 Lightning

## Do all forms with the same private theme update when you edit the private theme?

 No

 **Yes**



## Which control changes the background color of the page, behind the form?

 **Background Color**

 Form Background Color

 Read Only Background Color

 Form Header Background Color

## You've decided that you'd like to change the form's border color. What does the "A" in RGBA change? 

 The thickness of the border.

 The shape of the border.

 **The transparency of the border.**



### Processing



## Which of the following statements about E-Signatures are true? 

 **E-Signatures require a Premier plan or above.**

 **E-Signatures are compliant with the Uniform Electronic Transactions Act (UETA).**

 Your respondents must verify the E-Signature in order to submit the form.

 **You can collect initials along with signatures with the E-Signature feature.**



## If a form respondent chooses to make a correction to their form during Review Before Submit, will "Credit Card Number" and "CVV Code" fields be cleared for security purposes?

 **Yes**

 No



## Which icon will appear next to responses in the Responses page which have been saved and are not yet complete? 

 A green checkmark

 **An orange clock**

 A red "X"

 A yellow hourglass

Question 4: Correct answer

## How can Google reCAPTCHA improve your data collection? Choose all that apply.

 **It will require JavaScript to be enabled in the browser before submitting a form.**

 **It will prevent spam submissions from bots.**

 It will prevent all spam submissions.

 It will make all of your form fields required.



## Which of these are valid availability options? 

 **Restrict by Quota**

 **Active or Archived**

 Restrict by IP Address

 Restrict by Submission Value





## Is it possible to add the respondent's IP address as a column in your response report? 

 No

 **Yes**



## What is the difference between editing and reopening a response?

 Editing a response allows the respondent to submit new data, while reopening a response allows you to alter the response data.

 Reopening a response allows you to send a new password on forms with Save & Resume enabled. Editing a response allows you to alter the data and re-submit the form.

 **Editing a response allows you to alter the data and re-submit the form. Reopening a response allows you to send a new password to a respondent who has not completed a response, even if the Save & Resume option is not enabled for the form.**

## Which form publishing options will not require you to republish your form every time you make changes in the form builder?

 **FormAssembly Hosted Form**

 **WordPress Plugin**

 Embed HTML

 **iFrame**

## Which of these FormAssembly plans are able to download responses as PDFs? 

 **Enterprise**

 Professional

 **Premier**

 **Compliance Cloud**

## Which of these is not an available response layout? 

 Standard

 Compact

 Verbose

 **Simple**







## Who receives the Auto-Responder emails?

 The form creator.

 **The email collected in the form and set in the Notifications page.**

 The email used for Save & Resume.

 The email set in the Email Responses To field.



## The redirect formula has a character limit of 2,000 characters.

 **True**

 False



## Which of these plans cannot send PDFs of the responses? 

 Compliance Cloud

 **Professional**

 Premier

 Enterprise



## From this list, select the three aliases which can be used in custom Notification and Auto-Responder emails.

 IP_LIST

 **COMPLETION_TIME**

 **RESPONSE**

 **FORM_NAME**



## Where can you use formulas in the Notifications page?

 **Thank You Message**

 **Email Responses To**

 **Email Content**

 Sender Email



# Salesforce Connectors



## Is it possible to prefill a form without the Salesforce Prefill connector?

 **Yes**

 No



## Are you able to prefill data into a hidden field?

 No

 **Yes**



## Which types of objects can you use to prefill your form?

 **Salesforce Custom Objects**

 **Salesforce Standard Objects**

## How many records can the Salesforce Prefill connector prefill into a repeatable section? 

 **250**

 25

 100

 10

## Is it possible to prefill a drop-down menu in your form with a picklist in Salesforce that contains different choice options? 

 **Yes**

 No



## Can you use repeatable fields and sections in FormAssembly formulas?

 **No**

 Yes



## What is wrong with the following Skip-if formula?

@IF( %%tfa_12%%="Yes", "TRUE", "FALSE" )

 @IF() is not a valid formula.

 The alias should be surrounded by single % characters, not double.

 **It contains unnecessary spaces.**

 "True" and "False" should not be in all-caps.



## What does the “Get New Salesforce Objects (Refresh Schema)” option do? 

 **This option refreshes the connector's "view" of Salesforce and allows you to see any new custom objets and fields.**

 This option refreshes the connector's "view" of your form and shows any changes you have recently made in the Form Builder.

 This option reauthenticates your connector in order to resolve connection errors.



## How would you resolve the following error message in your Salesforce Connector?

*3.2. Create Contact - Use one of these records?*

 **On step 3.2, you would change the Create Contact step to Update the record instead in order to prevent violations of the Salesforce Standard Contact Duplicate Rule.**

 You never enabled a Duplicate rule in Salesforce, so this is a FormAssembly bug.

 You would remove the repeatable option from section 3.2 in your form.

 On step 3, you would change the Create Contact step to Update the record instead in order to prevent violations of the Salesforce Standard Contact Duplicate Rule.

## Which of these FormAssembly plans allow access to the Salesforce Prefill Connector?

 **Compliance Cloud**

 Professional

 **Premier**

 **Enterprise Cloud**







## If you would like to associate a file to a Contact record in Salesforce, where should you position the ContentVersion step in your connector? 

 As the parent of the dependent Contact step.

 Before the Contact step.

 **After the Contact step.**



## Which of these would definitely cause an error when submitting a form which sends file uploads to Salesforce Files?

 Uploading a file that is 35MB.

 Not uploading a file to the form despite adding a Skip-if formula to the ContentVersion step.

 Using a custom Title.

 **Not uploading a file to the form and not adding a Skip-if formula to the ContentVersion step.**



## Is it possible to send data from the E-Signature to custom objects in Salesforce?

 No

 **Yes**



## If you are sending a file to Attachments in Salesforce Classic, what is your file upload limit?

 15MB

 35MB

 **25MB**

 2GB



## Which of these is most likely to cause an error when respondents are submitting your form? 

 **Having a repeatable file upload field in your form which is not required.**

 Having a file upload field on your form which is not required, but having a Skip-if formula on the ContentVersion step.

 Having a required file upload field in your form and no Skip-if formula on the ContentVersion step.

 Creating a custom Title by using a formula in the mapping.





## Which of the following payment connectors allow both one-time and recurring payments in a **single connector**. 

 Chargent

 **Stripe**

 **iATS**

 PayPal

 **Authorize.net**



## Which of the following payment connectors do not have a recurring charge option?

 **PayPal**

 Authorize.net

 Stripe

 iATS

 Chargent



## Which of the following payment connectors are available on ALL FormAssembly plans? 

 **PayPal**

 Authorize.net

 **Chargent**

 **iATS**

 **Stripe**

## How many different Chargent packages can be used with the Chargent connector?

 4

 2

 **3**

 1



## Which payment connector requires you to have a Salesforce Connector set up in addition to the payment connector?

 Stripe

 CyberSource

 **Chargent**

 Authorize.net





## Which of these FormAssembly plans are able to add Respondent Authentication to their forms?

 Professional

 **Compliance Cloud**

 **Enterprise Cloud**

 Premier



## Only Enterprise Cloud and Compliance Cloud plans can use the HTTPS Connector. 

 True

 **False**

## Which Respondent Authentication methods also work with prefill connectors?

 SAML

 Salesforce Communities (Experiences)

 CAS

 **All of the above**



## Which of these cannot be exported to Google Sheets by the connector?

 Checkboxes

 **Files**

 Text Fields

 Radio Buttons



## The HTTPS Connector can pass data as JSON content.

 True

 **False**





## Which of these are required to use FormAssembly in Salesforce? 

 **Both usernames must match.**

 **Install the most recent version of the app.**

 A FormAssembly Enterprise or Compliance Cloud account.

 **Assign specific Apex Classes to Guest and Community Users before adding forms to Communities.**



## The FormAssembly AppExchange app allows you to open FormAssembly inside of as many Salesforce instances as you'd like. 

 True

 **False**



## Which of these methods can you use to contact our Support Team? 

 **Email support@formassembly.com**

 **Fill out the Support Request form**

 Phone

 **Click the Chat button under the Help menu**



## Who can you contact in order to have a FormAssembly expert build your form for you? 

 Customer Support

 **Implementation Services**

 Sales

 Customer Success Managers



Which of these FormAssembly plans do not allow you to use Salesforce Dynamic Picklists in your forms?

 Compliance Cloud

 **Premier**

 **Professional**

 Enterprise Cloud
